  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee Guidelines\n\n2. Typical Legal Provisions\n- Criminalization of money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n\n3. Key Legislative Components\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Criminal investigations\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential criminal prosecution\n\n5. Reporting Obligations\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Cash transaction reporting\n- Cross-border transfer declarations\n\n6. Jurisdictional Considerations\n- Varying regulations across different countries\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n- Extradition treaties\n\nThis framework aims to prevent financial crimes and track illicit financial flows.",
